solution: class Solution {
public:
    int alternateDigitSum(int n) {
        int sum = 0, sign = 1;
        while (n) {
            sum += sign * (n % 10);
            sign *= -1;
            n /= 10;
        }
        return (sign == 1) ? -sum : sum;
    }
};
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(log n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Traverse digits from least-significant to most-significant, flipping sign each step. After the loop, if the final sign is positive, the most-significant digit was subtracted, so negate the result; otherwise leave it.

